  <section aria-labelledby="why">
    <h2 id="why">Why this toolkit exists</h2>
    <p>
      As a repo grows, the biggest risks arenâ€™t the features â€” itâ€™s drift: broken links, inconsistent slugs,
      missing tags, duplicated pages, and last-minute surprises where preview and production donâ€™t match.
      This toolkit is the safety layer that turns those risks into repeatable checks and safe workflows.
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Fast:</strong> small commands you can run daily.</li>
      <li><strong>Safe:</strong> guardrails for risky operations (release prep, rewrites, restores).</li>
      <li><strong>Reproducible:</strong> the same steps work across projects.</li>
      <li><strong>Explainable:</strong> every script has a â€œwhen to useâ€ and â€œwhat it changes.â€</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="muted">
      Use this page as your checklist: create â†’ validate â†’ preview â†’ release â†’ deploy â†’ recover.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Jump to:</strong>
